  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "In [Beacon chain processing](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/master/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#beacon-chain-processing) there is a block processing requirement that: \r\n\r\n> The node has processed its `state` up to slot, `block.slot - 1`.\r\n\r\nIn [Per-block processing](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/master/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#per-block-processing), there is a statement:\r\n\r\n> Verify that `block.slot == state.slot`\r\n\r\nI understand the intentions here but I think these statements contradict.\r\n\r\nI suspect the first statement is a relic from back when there was a `while` loop during block processing.",
